    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house, is a trust account that holds funds until certain conditions are met. It's a way to ensure that the transaction proceeds smoothly and that all parties fulfill their obligations. Think of it like a temporary holding cell for your down payment and closing costs, where the funds are safely kept until the closing date. You don't actually need to keep the funds in the escrow account, but rather, the funds are held by a third-party escrow agent, like a bank or a title company, on behalf of the buyer and seller. This way, the funds are protected and released only when the transaction is complete.",
      "source": "target",
