    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so basically someone else just holds the money so neither side gets cheated? who exactly is the person or company that usually manages this? is it just a random bank or something specific?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent is usually a title company or a lawyer's escrow account, but it can also be a bank or a specialized escrow service. The key is that it's a neutral third party, not the bank you have your account with, and not the realtor or the seller. They're like a referee in the transaction, making sure everything gets paid on time and according to the agreement. In Toronto, you're likely to work with a title company or a lawyer who has an escrow account, as they're familiar with the local real estate laws and regulations.",
